# Whisper.cpp Integration

ToolMate integrates [Whisper.cpp](https://github.com/ggerganov/whisper.cpp) for supporting voice entry.

# Set up Whisper.cpp

You need to set up whisper.cpp separately, e.g.:

> cd ~

> git clone https://github.com/ggerganov/whisper.cpp.git

> cd whisper.cpp

> make

In this example, the path of the whisper main file should be:

> ~/whisper.cpp/main

Make a note of this path for further configuration.

For more information, read https://github.com/ggerganov/whisper.cpp

# Set up ToolMate AI

Enter a blank entry '' in ToolMate AI prompt and select 'change voice typing config' from the action menu.

Alternately, enter '.voicetypingconfig' directly in ToolMate AI prompt.

1. Select 'whispercpp'

<img width="842" alt="whispercpp" src="https://github.com/eliranwong/toolmate/assets/25262722/d6574aaa-2f2b-4fb3-b750-219e56cb254b">

2. Enter the path of the whisper main file

3. Select a whisper model

<img width="842" alt="whisper_models" src="https://github.com/eliranwong/toolmate/assets/25262722/5c8d2df2-17c7-4cd5-9de2-25f92194053c">

4. Follow the rest of the dialog